### When do I need to complete the work?
Work will need to be completed within 3 months of the delivery of the grant?

### You already have an R/Ruby/JS/Pyton library, can i still apply?
No. We are only able to support a single implementation of the libraries per languarge.

### My programming language of choice is not included in the list. Can I still apply?
Yes, please do. The above list is our initial assessment of high-impact languages for data analysis, but we may have overlooked one or two.

### How will we make our choice?
We will base our choice on evidence of technical capabilities and also favour applicants who have a particular interest in working with the Frictionless Data Specifications. Also preference will be given to applicants who have an interest working with and maintaining these libraries going forward.

### When is the deadline?
Expressions of interest should be received by the 1st of April, but this may be extended. The fund will close on the 31st of July 2017.

### What will the agreement look like?
We will have a Memorandum of Understanding between Open Knowledge International and the Applicant, based on some agreed deliverables derived from the Implementation reference documentation

### How will Open Knowledge International support me in the work?
One of the reasons that we are initiating this is to further improve the specifications and how we implement them. Our developers will be on hand to work closely with you as you complete the work. Further to this we announce implementers as technical partners on the project website and will be happy to support you by promoting your organization's work through our blog and network channels.
